Section 1: Q&A; Pairs

Example 1.1

User

What is precision vs recall?
AI Response

Precision is correct positive predictions / all positive predictions. Recall is correct positive predictions / all
actual positives. F1 score harmonically balances both.

Example 1.2

User

What is word embedding?
AI Response

Word embeddings map words to dense vectors where similar words are nearby. Word2Vec, GloVe, and
FastText are popular methods, used as NLP model input features.

Example 1.3

User

What is transfer learning?
AI Response

Transfer learning reuses a model trained on one task as a starting point for another related task, reducing
training time and data requirements significantly.

Example 1.4

User

What is machine learning?
AI Response

Machine learning is a branch of artificial intelligence that enables systems to learn and improve from
experience without being explicitly programmed.

Example 1.5

User

What is GPT?
AI Response

GPT (Generative Pre-trained Transformer) is an autoregressive language model trained to predict the next
token. GPT-3 and GPT-4 are large-scale versions capable of diverse language tasks.

Example 1.6

User

What is zero-shot learning?
AI Response

Zero-shot learning predicts unseen classes by leveraging semantic relationships or natural language task
descriptions, allowing LLMs to generalize without task-specific training.

Example 1.7

User

What is dropout?
AI Response



Dropout randomly sets a fraction of neuron activations to zero during training, preventing co-adaptation of
neurons and reducing overfitting.

Example 1.8

User

What is reinforcement learning?
AI Response

Reinforcement learning trains an agent to make decisions by interacting with an environment and receiving
rewards or penalties, aiming to maximize cumulative reward over time.

Example 1.9

User

What is feature engineering?
AI Response

Feature engineering creates or transforms input variables using domain knowledge to improve model
performance. It includes scaling, encoding, and creating interaction terms.

Example 1.10

User

What is a hyperparameter?
AI Response

A hyperparameter is a configuration setting external to the model—like learning rate or batch size—set
before training and tuned using validation performance.



